tool_list.tool name: Ali Express Data Service: Seller Info
tool_list.tool description:
Retrieves detailed seller info. **Note:** The `sellerId` parameter should not be confused with the Store Number displayed on the AliExpress website. Using an incorrect `sellerId` will result in a "not found" error message. Kindly check [this](https://ibb.co/pP4WVPh) image for more clarification:

For the `item/itemInfo` endpoint, in the response you could find the id from the JSON path `seller_info.nickname`:
```json
 "seller_info": {
        "nickname": "239194804", <---- use this
        "features": {
            "url": "https://www.aliexpress.com/store/1101351612", <--- don't use this
            "id": "246855432",
            "country": "China",
            "percentage": "93",
            "code": "EE",
            "count": "503222",
            "starts": "1022610600",
            "years": "3",
            "fans_num": "917861",
            "logo": "https://ae01.alicdn.com/kf/Sd8de4bd7006644ea8821899a1f864918u.png"
        }
```
For the `item/itemAppInfo` endpoint, in the response you could find the id from the JSON path `productInfoComponent.adminSeq`:
```json
 "productInfoComponent": {
        "adminSeq": 239194804, <---- use this
        "categoryId": 70805,
        "categoryPaths": "7/200001081/200001082/70805",
        "fromTaobao": false,
        "id": 1005005120789585,
        "idStr": "1005005120789585",
        "lot": false,
        "maxPrice": 81.06,
        "minPrice": 77.5,
        "multiCurrencyDisplayPrice": "$77.50 - $81.06",
        "multiUnitName": "Pieces",
        "numberPerLot": 1,
        "oddUnitName": "piece",
        "openOfferPriceRule": true,
        "propGroups": [],
        "src": "approved",
    }
```

I found a specific model on Amazon (B08L8L9G3Q) and similar ones on Wayfair (W003078383) and AliExpress (4000961087745). Could you help me compare them? I want to know about warranty options, financing on the Wayfair one, shipping from AliExpress to the US, and what categories these chairs fall under for both Asos and Alibaba for future reference. Also, I'd need to calculate the total cost with taxes for the Amazon chair, and since the AliExpress price is in Chinese yuan, I'd need that converted to USD. Oh, and I have a photo of my office space - could you remove the background so I can visualize how the chair would look?
